#: ../../digest/digest.rst:10
msgid ""
"This module provides the basis for creating key performance indicators, "
"including static and dynamic thresholds (SQL query or Python code), on "
"local and remote data sources."
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:14
msgid ""
"The module also provides the mechanism to update KPIs automatically. A "
"scheduler is executed every hour and updates the KPI values, based on the"
" periodicity of each KPI. KPI computation can also be done manually."
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:18
msgid ""
"Find the menu of KPI Digest from :menuselection:`Settings --> Technical "
"--> Email --> Digest Emails`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:21
msgid "How to create Digest Email"
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:23
msgid "There are four types of periodicity."
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:25
msgid "Daily"
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:26
msgid "Weekly"
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:27
msgid "Monthly"
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:28
msgid "Quarterly"
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:30
msgid ""
"The periodicity describes it self. Whichever periodicity is selected will"
" work according to the period. As the user changes the periodicity, the "
"**Next Send Date** will change according to its time period."
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:34
msgid ""
"Recipient is the one who receives the emails from the system. The user "
"can stop getting email from the system by clicking on **Unsubscribe me** "
"button from the header."
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:38
msgid ""
"The system provides the default Email Template to show off the digest "
"data. User can also create their own Email Template."
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:43
msgid ""
"Under KPIs tab, there are some fields which will be considered as the "
"source of the data. The user can preview the template by clicking on the "
"smart button labeled as Preview."
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:47
msgid ""
"Let's say, If user wants number of connected users, messages, revenue and"
" email partner then mark the checkbox against that label. Only those data"
" will be available in preview whichever field is marked as true."
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:52
msgid "How to customize your digest?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:54
msgid ""
"Under **How to customize your digest?** tab, user is given two buttons "
"labeled as **Add Customized Digest** and **Remove Customized Digest** "
"where user can add their own customized digest and can remove their own."
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:60
msgid ""
"The user is given the instruction to customize the digest under the "
"buttons."
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:63
msgid "Add Customized Digest"
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:65
msgid ""
"By customizing the digest, it will create a field with a type of "
"checkbox, which will be reflected in the digest report."
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:70
msgid ""
"The name of the **Compute Field Name** and **Compute Function** will be "
"changed as the user changes the name under **Field Name** field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:73
msgid "**Label Name** is the label how the field will be labeled with."
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:75
msgid ""
"The next step is to set the position of the field. The field has to be "
"inside the group. So the user has to select the group from **Group "
"Name**. It will only show those groups which are under KPIs tab."
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:79
msgid "There are three positions of the field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:81
msgid "Before"
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:82
msgid "After"
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:83
msgid "Inside"
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:85
msgid ""
"If the user selects **Before** or **After**, that means the user has to "
"create a new group and will be set according to the position. The field "
"will be generated inside that newly created group."
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:91
msgid ""
"If the user selects **Inside**, that means the newly created filed will "
"be set inside the selected group."
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:96
msgid ""
"The system will retrieve the data according to the filter. To set filter "
"over data, select the model and add filter by clicking on green button "
"labeled as **+Add Filter**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:100
msgid "That will allow the user to select the field and the value against it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:102
msgid "The python preview will be shown that how the filter is applied."
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:104
msgid ""
"the compute field name will be generated based on the field name. The "
"user is supposed to set the type of the field either it should be "
"**Integer** or **Monetary**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:110
msgid ""
"The system will generate the code according to the models and filters, "
"which creates a compute function and will retrieve the desired data."
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:119
msgid ""
"The user is also given the help under **Help** tab, which will help to "
"develop the compute filed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:124
msgid ""
"Once the procedure is completed, the filed will be added at appropriate "
"and desired place. The data of that field will be available if the field "
"(checkbox) is marked as **True**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:131
msgid "Remove Customized Digest"
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:133
msgid ""
"The user can remove the unnecessary customized digest. On clicking "
"**Remove Customized Digest** button, a parametrized window will pop up."
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:136
msgid ""
"There will be two options under **Remove Type** field, **Group** and "
"**Field**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:138
msgid ""
"If Group is selected, then it is necessary to select the Group under "
"**Available Group**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:140
msgid ""
"If Field is selected, then it is necessary to select the digest field "
"under **Field**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../digest/digest.rst:144
msgid ""
"The system will remove the Group or the Field under the Group from the "
"checkbox list."
msgstr ""

